The paper proposes a new graph-based clustering method that involves learning a structured similarity graph, enforcing a discrete transformation on the intermediate continuous label, and designing an adaptive robust module. These techniques are all related to machine learning and optimization, which are commonly found in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper also mentions experiments conducted on image datasets, which suggests a possible connection to the sub-categories of cs.SI (Sound and Image Processing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
